8 (6) (a) A majority of the members of the task force constitutes a quorum.
9 (b) The action of a majority of a quorum constitutes an action of the task force.
10 (7) The task force shall:
11 (a) develop knowledge and expertise regarding issues pertaining to blockchain, financial
12 technology, and digital innovation technology; and
13 (b) develop and introduce recommendations regarding policy pertaining to:
14 (i) the promotion in the state of the adoption of blockchain, financial technology, and digital
15 innovation;
16 (ii) the development of nonfinancial incentives for industries in the state related to blockchain,
17 financial technology, and digital innovation;
18 (iii) the promotion of partnerships with existing financial institutions and regulated financial service
19 entities with respect to blockchain, financial technology, and digital innovation; and
20 (iv) the regulation in the state of blockchain, financial technology, and digital innovation.
21 (8) The task force shall report its findings and recommendations to the economic affairs interim
22 committee and the legislative council by July 1, 2026.
